OL,3,CCalls to protect 'in danger'
OL,4,CGuernsey's Loophole towers from
OL,5,Ccollapse
OL,7,F"They're a particularly Guernsey
OL,8,Fthing. They belong to a very specific
OL,9,Fperiod (and) they don't occur anywhere
OL,10,Felse so I believe we need to look
OL,11,Fafter them."
OL,13,FThe towers were built by the British
OL,14,Fbetween 1778 and 1779 to keep out the
OL,15,FFrench who were supporting the
OL,16,FAmerican Civil War.
OL,18,FThe loopholes are named after the
OL,19,Flarge number of musket firing holes
OL,20,Fand have survived centuries of storms
OL,21,Fand the Occupation.
