OL,3,CCalls to protect 'in danger'
OL,4,CGuernsey's Loophole towers from
OL,5,Ccollapse
OL,7,FWhile some towers are States-owned,
OL,8,Fothers, such as Fermain Tower which
OL,9,Fwas given to Guernsey's National
OL,10,FTrust, are privately owned.
OL,12,FWhen the Trust was bequeathed Fermain
OL,13,FTower - also known as the "Pepper Pot"
OL,14,F- they spent years turning it into
OL,15,Fself-accommodation to protect it.
